      <section id="uid7">
        <title>Multilinearity</title>
        <para id="id169638">The operation of convolution is linear in each of the two function variables. Additivity in each variable results from distributivity of convolution over addition. Homogenity of order one in each variable results from the fact that for all continuous time signals <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub></m:mrow></m:math> and scalars <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>a</m:mi></m:math> the following relationship holds.</para><equation id="id169675">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>a</m:mi>
              <m:mrow>
